==Transportation==
The three easiest ways to reach [[Forthos Dungeon]] include:
*[[Xeric's talisman]] - Teleporting to Xeric's Glade brings players just east of the eastern dungeon entrance.
*[[Kharedst's memoirs]]/[[Book of the dead]] - Using the "Lunch by the lancalliums" teleport brings the player by the [[River Hos]] just north-east of the dungeon entrances.
*[[Spirit tree]] (player-grown) just south of the dungeon entrance.

==Mechanics==
[[File:Fighting Sarachnis.png|thumb|right|A player fights Sarachnis, the mother of the temple spiders.]]
Sarachnis has several attacks that she will occasionally use other than the standard melee and ranged attacks. Her melee attacks consist of smashing the player with her legs, while she launches barbed projectiles as her ranged attack. 

* '''Healing strike''' - Sarachnis' standard attacks will heal her on [[successful hit]]s, indicated by a [[File:Heal hitsplat.png]] magenta [[hitsplat]]. She heals 5 health for every successful melee attack, and 10 health for every successful ranged attack, regardless of how much damage she actually deals, including zeros.
* '''Sticky web''' - Every four standard attacks, Sarachnis will screech out {{overhead|Hsss!}} and shoot out a sticky web that leaves players bound for 6 [[ticks]] (3.6 seconds), then moving a short distance away from where she was before attacking the player. This attack can be completely negated by wearing [[aranea boots]], and the bind effect can be partially mitigated with a [[transformation ring]] (see [[#Strategy]]).
* '''Spawns''' - When Sarachnis reaches 66% and 33% health, she summons two [[Spawn of Sarachnis]] per player; a level 68 that uses Magic and has a maximum hit of 11, and a level 107 that uses Melee and has a maximum hit of 13. Both have 30 health.

==Suggested skills==
*{{SCP|Hitpoints|65+}} 
*{{SCP|Strength|65+}} 
*{{SCP|Attack|65+}} (required to equip weapons like [[Sarachnis cudgel]])
*{{SCP|Defence|65+}} (to be able to tank some damage from minions)
*{{SCP|Magic|60+}} (for magic defence against mage minion)
*{{SCP|Ranged|70+}} (for magic defence armour)
*{{SCP|Prayer|43+}} (for protection prayers, 70 recommended for [[Piety]])

==Strategy==
Sarachnis is weak to crush weapons, and has high magic and ranged defence. Therefore, it is recommended to bring high strength bonus equipment and a crush weapon that can attack fast (such as an [[abyssal bludgeon]]).

Sarachnis attacks with melee when players are next to her, and Ranged when she cannot reach them; it is advised to pray Protect from Melee or Protect from Missiles accordingly, as these attacks can hit up to 31 if they aren't protected against, and also heal her if they do manage to hit. Her melee range is deceptively large, so players are advised to exercise caution when standing near her.
[[File:Sarachnis - Web Skipping.mp4|thumb|400px|A player demonstrates the Web Skipping manoeuvre with the ring of coins.]]

Additionally, lower-levelled players may wish to kill the blue magic-using [[Spawn of Sarachnis]]. The melee spawns may be tanked with sufficiently high defensive bonuses, but are not necessary to kill as the player should be praying Protect from Melee outside her web attack.  

Players fighting Sarachnis can avoid getting snared by her web attack by either wearing [[aranea boots]] throughout the fight, or by equipping the [[ring of stone]] immediately after her web appears under the player. This allows the player to attack more frequently and avoid taking ranged attacks at all, avoiding prayer switches entirely. (The [[ring of nature]] and [[ring of coins]] are equally viable options; the [[Easter ring]] delays for an extra tick, which is too slow to avoid ranged attacks, but is better than nothing.) If these strategies are not able to be used, eating food '''only''' while bound by her web is recommended to maximize damage dealt.

All tiles directly adjacent to walls are out of Sarachnis's melee range. Standing on one of these tiles and praying Protect from Missiles will nullify all of her damage, but not the damage of her spawn.

When Sarachnis is killed, any remaining spawns will automatically die off with her. She will respawn in 17 ticks (10.2s).

